00:16:58.410 --> 00:17:00.360 align:middle line:84%
competing for sunlight
in the forest,

00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:02.790 align:middle line:84%
and the big tree will
get up to the sun first,

00:17:02.790 --> 00:17:05.490 align:middle line:84%
and the little tree will be
in the shade and will die.

00:17:05.490 --> 00:17:07.920 align:middle line:84%
And I just read this book
"Secret Life of Trees,"

00:17:07.920 --> 00:17:09.630 align:middle line:84%
and it turns out
it's the opposite--

00:17:09.630 --> 00:17:12.119 align:middle line:84%
that the big tree that's
getting the sunlight

00:17:12.119 --> 00:17:14.859 align:middle line:84%
shares its nutrients
through the soil--

00:17:14.859 --> 00:17:16.740 align:middle line:84%
which is not dirt;
soil's alive--

00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:20.849 align:middle line:84%
through a matrix of mycelia,
of mushrooms in the soil,

00:17:20.849 --> 00:17:22.200 align:middle line:90%
with the little tree.

00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:24.283 align:middle line:84%
And then the little tree
gets all those nutrients.

00:17:24.283 --> 00:17:26.849 align:middle line:84%
Then, in the winter, when the
big tree loses its leaves,

00:17:26.849 --> 00:17:29.040 align:middle line:84%
the little tree, which
is usually an evergreen,

00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:32.520 align:middle line:84%
passes nutrients back
through those same mushrooms,

00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:36.390 align:middle line:84%
take a service fee, and give the
nutrients back to the big tree.

00:17:36.390 --> 00:17:39.480 align:middle line:84%
So the two trees are
not competing for sun.

00:17:39.480 --> 00:17:40.920 align:middle line:90%
They're collaborating.

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:44.880 align:middle line:84%
They have diverse
strategies of survival,

00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:51.550 align:middle line:84%
which allows the forest,
as a collective organism,

00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:53.200 align:middle line:90%
to support itself.

00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:57.520 align:middle line:84%
So if human beings are
the most advanced species

00:17:57.520 --> 00:17:59.290 align:middle line:84%
on the evolutionary
trail-- which

00:17:59.290 --> 00:18:01.180 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that we
