to death or the risk of choking

00:18:34.150 --> 00:18:36.370 align:middle line:84%
to death in order to be able
to speak with each other

00:18:36.370 --> 00:18:38.290 align:middle line:90%
and collaborate on those levels.

00:18:38.290 --> 00:18:39.880 align:middle line:84%
And I look at each
medium that we

00:18:39.880 --> 00:18:43.600 align:middle line:84%
create is an extension of
that collaborative urge--

00:18:43.600 --> 00:18:46.160 align:middle line:84%
you know, from writing,
and television, and radio,

00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:47.230 align:middle line:90%
and even the internet.

00:18:47.230 --> 00:18:50.860 align:middle line:84%
But then, we flip
it on itself, and we

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.360 align:middle line:90%
don't use it to collaborate.

00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:55.930 align:middle line:84%
We use it to dominate
and to extract.

00:18:55.930 --> 00:18:59.890 align:middle line:84%
The internet does not establish
rapport between people.

00:18:59.890 --> 00:19:03.550 align:middle line:84%
The internet does the
opposite now intentionally.

00:19:03.550 --> 00:19:11.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a de-socializing medium
that restricts our creativity

00:19:11.170 --> 00:19:18.070 align:middle line:84%
and represses our actual
humanity, our weirdness,

00:19:18.070 --> 00:19:21.970 align:middle line:84%
our soul, our
ingenuity is treated

00:19:21.970 --> 00:19:26.230 align:middle line:90%
by the digital realm as noise.

00:19:26.230 --> 00:19:28.450 align:middle line:90%
And I think that's the signal.

