at how do we develop more

00:54:04.030 --> 00:54:06.860 align:middle line:90%
regenerative economic models?

00:54:06.860 --> 00:54:11.980 align:middle line:84%
How do we implement local
currencies and alternative

00:54:11.980 --> 00:54:13.510 align:middle line:90%
currencies?

00:54:13.510 --> 00:54:18.190 align:middle line:84%
How do we start looking
at resources as commons

00:54:18.190 --> 00:54:21.730 align:middle line:84%
rather than as commodities
and understand how

00:54:21.730 --> 00:54:28.280 align:middle line:90%
to steward a resource together.

00:54:28.280 --> 00:54:35.820 align:middle line:84%
So I think that there are some
simple, good, actionable steps

00:54:35.820 --> 00:54:39.870 align:middle line:84%
that we can take towards
relocalizing our economies,

00:54:39.870 --> 00:54:44.850 align:middle line:84%
accumulating less, learning
how to respect and take

00:54:44.850 --> 00:54:47.310 align:middle line:84%
care of elders so that
people don't feel the need

00:54:47.310 --> 00:54:51.102 align:middle line:84%
to create a giant war chest
